.TH "tpm2_get_random" 9 "tpm2_get_random" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
tpm2_get_random \- get random bytes from the TPM RNG
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" tpm2_get_random
.BI "(struct tpm_chip *chip "  ","
.BI "u8 *dest "  ","
.BI "size_t max "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "chip" 12
a \fItpm_chip\fP instance
.IP "dest" 12
destination buffer
.IP "max" 12
the max number of random bytes to pull
.SH "RETURN"
size of the buffer on success,
-errno otherwise (positive TPM return codes are masked to -EIO)
